The population of each generation consists of a fixed number of DAGs. Each DAG represents gene relationships. The genetic algorithm’s aim is to move from the current population of DAGs to a new generation where the overall quality improves (as measured by the Norris-Patton likelihood). The elitist strategy only moves the top \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
